g for the theatre.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]Shuttered since San Jos Rep closed in June 2014, the Hammer Theatre reopened in March 2016 as a distinctive, high-quality performance venue in the heart of downtown San Jos. Operated by San Jos State University, the theatre serves the university and the community through high-qualityprogramming expressive of the unique characteristics and diverse cultures that comprise Silicon Valley.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\n<h1>Hammer Theatre Team</h1>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Executive Director  Christopher Burrill</li>\n 	<li>Director of Client Services  Lisa Laymon</li>\n 	<li>Client Services &amp; Event Coordinator  Hannah Hudgins</li>\n 	<li>Director of Marketing  Sheryl Spann</li>\n 	<li>Director of Patron Services  Maria Bones</li>\n 	<li>Production Manager  Anthony Sutton</li>\n 	<li>Performing Arts Technician  Ted Kamp</li>\n 	<li>Director of Technology &amp; Facilities  Jim LeFever</li>\n 	<li>Associate Director of Technology &amp; Facilities  Keay Edwards</li>\n</ul>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/4\"][vc_single_image image=\"81\" img_size=\"full\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/4\"][vc_single_image image=\"78\" img_size=\"full\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/4\"][vc_single_image image=\"77\" img_size=\"full\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/4\"][vc_single_image image=\"76\" img_size=\"full\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=\"2/3\"][vc_column_text]\n<h1>Performance Venues</h1>\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\n<h2>Sobrato Auditorium</h2>\n<ul>\n 	<li>532 seats with excellent sightlines</li>\n 	<li>Three seating sections\n1) Orchestra: 158 seats + 8 wheelchair\n2) Paterre: 201 seats\n3) Balcony: 157 seats + 8 wheelchair</li>\n 	<li>Large state, including orchestra pit</li>\n 	<li>41\' Proscenium opening</li>\n 	<li>34\' Stage depth</li>\n 	<li>Orchestra pit can add 12\' depth at center 6\' 