20:18:46','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/?page_id=25',0,'page','',0),(26,3,'2017-11-17 22:32:06','2017-11-17 22:32:06','[vc_row el_class=\"paddingLeft paddingRight margin-bottom-60\"][vc_column][vc_images_carousel images=\"401,397\" img_size=\"full\" onclick=\"custom_link\" custom_links_target=\"_blank\" custom_links=\"#E-8_aHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZ5b3V0dS5iZSUyRlktQlU3YWdMU1kw\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"paddingLeft paddingRight padding-bottom-30\"][vc_column][vc_column_text]\n<h1>About The Hammer</h1>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"paddingLeft paddingRight padding-bottom-30\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\" el_class=\"padding-right-20\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"margin-right-20\"]The Hammer Theatre, named after former San Jos Mayor Susan Hammer and her husband Phil Hammer, a San Jos Rep Board Trustee, was completed in 1997 via a collaboration between the San Jos Redevelopment Agency and San Jos Repertory Theatre Company. This distinctive theatre offered theatrical productions for over seven years for San Jose and Bay area patrons and to national acclaim.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]In March 2016, San Jos State University reopened the Hammer Theatre as a distinctive, high-quality performance venue in the heart of downtown San Jos. The theatre serves San Joses community and the university through high-qualityprogramming expressive of the unique characteristics and diverse cultures that comprise Silicon Valley.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"paddingLeft paddingRight\"][vc_column width=\"1/3\"][vc_column_text]\n<p class=\"font-size-24\" style=\"font-weight: 500;\">Goal</p>\n<p class=\"margin-bottom-30\">To reactivate the Hammer Theatre Center, a distinctive, high quality performance venue in downtown San Jose, with dynamic and diversified programming while building a collaborative partnership for Arts, Innovation, and Technology that will express the multi-cultural, multi-ethnic, creative performing arts community of San Jose and Silicon Valley.</p>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/3\" el_class=\"padding-left-20\"][vc_column_text]\n<p class=\"font-size-24\" style=\"font-weight: 500;\">Mission</p>\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Operated by San Jos State University, the Hammer Theatre has a three-pronged mission:</span>\n<ul class=\"margin-bottom-30\">\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Serve the San Jose community by building collaborative partnerships for arts, innovation and technology plus offering performing arts events or academic lectures that express the multi-cultural, highly creative and technologically progressive community of San Jose and Silicon Valley</span></li>\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Serve San Jose State University through offering artistically and educationallyexcellent programming that showcases the universitys premier performing arts plus presents world-class academic programs or lectures</span></li>\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Offer a 21</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">st</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> century performing arts center paradigm as the Hammer Theatre offers events across all genres (music, theatre, dance, speakers) within several sub-brands to meet the broad arts and educational appetite of a diverse community</span></li>\n</ul>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/3\" el_class=\"padding-left-20\"][vc_column_text]\n<p class=\"font-size-24\" style=\"font-weight: 500;\">Vision</p>\n<p class=\"margin-bottom-30\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Hammer Theatre Center is a unique performing arts facility that serves as anexus between the university, San Jos and the Bay Area andlocal or global talent. We offer innovative programming thatreflects Silicon Valleys culture of creativity, diversity, and technology. Audiences can experience live music, theatre, dance or progressive multimedia performances, National Theatre Live screenings or National Geographic Live lectures.</span></p>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"paddingLeft paddingRight\" css=\".vc_custom_1520031866171{margin-top: 20px !important;}\"][vc_column][vc_raw_html][/vc_raw_html][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"paddingLeft paddingRight margin-bottom-80\"][vc_column][vc_raw_html][/vc_raw_html][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"paddingLeft paddingRight margin-bottom-50\"][vc_column][vc_column_text]\n<h1>Performance &amp; Entertainment Venues</h1>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"paddingLeft paddingRight\"][vc_column width=\"2/3\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1521881052326{padding-right: 20px !important;}\"]\n<p class=\"font-size-24\" style=\"font-weight: 500;\">Sobrato Auditorium</p>\nMain theatre with 532 seats and excellent sightlines\n<ul style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">\n 	<li>Three seating sections\n1) Orchestra: 158 seats + 8 wheelchair\n2) Paterre: 201 seats\n3) Balcony: 157 seats + 8 wheelchair</li>\n 	<li>Large state, including orchestra pit with 41\' Proscenium opening and 34\' Stage depth</li>\n 	<li>Orchestra pit can add 12\' depth at center 6\' at sides when used as thrust/apron</li>\n 	<li>State-of-the-art acoustic system, Constellation virtual audio shell and up-to-date stage lighting</li>\n</ul>\n[/vc_column_text][vc_btn title=\"VIEW SEATING CHART\" shape=\"square\" align=\"left\" el_id=\"custom-button\" link=\"url:http%3A%2F%2Fhammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F02%2FHammer_Seating.pdf|title:Hammer%20Theatre%20Seating%20Chart|target:%20_blank|\" el_class=\"width-40-percent  \"][vc_column_text el_class=\"margin-top-30\"]\n<p class=\"font-size-24\" style=\"font-weight: 500;\">Hammer 4</p>\nBlack box performance space with 150 seats capacity\n<ul>\n 	<li>Meeting and reception space</li>\n 	<li>Available as rehearsal studio</li>\n</ul>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/3\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"margin-right\"]\n<p class=\"font-size-24\" style=\"font-weight: 500;\">Curtain Call Cafe Lounge</p>\n<p class=\"margin-bottom-20\">Ground floor space with a bar for special gathering</p>\n<p class=\"font-size-24\" style=\"font-weight: 500;\">Mercury News Lounge</p>\n<p class=\"margin-bottom-20\">Second floor lounge with a bar for private parties</p>\n<p class=\"font-size-24\" style=\"font-weight: 500;\">Rooftop Terrace</p>\n<p class=\"margin-bottom-20\">A versatile outdoor space with breathtaking sunset reception and parties</p>\n<p class=\"font-size-24\" style=\"font-weight: 500;\">Other Facilities</p>\n\n<ul class=\"margin-bottom-20\">\n 	<li>Dressing rooms</li>\n 	<li>Bar/concessions area</li>\n 	<li>2nd floor lobby</li>\n 	<li>Outside balconies.</li>\n</ul>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1520911945984{margin-bottom: 80px !important;}\" el_class=\"paddingLeft paddingRight  margin-top-80\"][vc_column][vc_raw_html][/vc_raw_html][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"background-hammerBlue flex-row-center paddingLeft paddingRight  margin-bottom-80 margin-top-80\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"white-text \"]\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">UPCOMING EVENTS</h1>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\" el_class=\"margin-btm-0\"][vc_raw_html][/vc_raw_html][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text][location_map][/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]','About','','publish','closed','closed','','about','','','2018-05-22 11:59:34','2018-05-22 18:59:34','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/?page_id=26',0,'page','',0),(27,3,'2017-11-17 22:32:06','2017-11-17 22:32:06','[vc_row el_class=\"paddingLeft paddingRight margin-top-20 margin-bottom-50\"][vc_column][vc_column_text]\n<h2></h2>\nOur goal at the Hammer Theatre is to provide you with the highest level of patron support and service while offering a great performance experience. Your questions are very important 