','','EVENTS & TICKETS','','publish','closed','closed','','events-tickets','','','2018-06-18 12:29:03','2018-06-18 19:29:03','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/2017/12/events-tickets/',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(115,3,'2017-12-12 19:55:51','2017-12-12 19:55:51','As part of Hammer Theatre\'s new ArtTech Series, ElevenPlay is a notable Japanese dance troupe known for incorporating advanced technologies into their works. Their use of projected multimedia, drones, and advanced three-dimensional objects attracted the attention of Americas Got Talent in 2016, where they debuted in front of millions of Americans. Reviewers raved over their performance as an experience of pure talent, ingenuity, and beauty. In addition, ElevenPlay has performed extensively in Japan, Europe, and Mexico. Dont miss the chance of watching the alluring performance of this multimedia dance troupe.\r\n\r\nDaito Manabe, a media artist, and Rhizomatiks, an interaction design company, who have collaborated with artists such as Bjork, OKGo, Squarepusher, and Nosaj Thing, have provided complete technical support to this ElevenPlay tour.','ArtTech Series  ElevenPlay','As part of Hammer Theatre\'s new ArtTech Series, ElevenPlay is a notable Japanese dance troupe known for incorporating advanced technologies into their works. ','publish','closed','closed','','arttech-series-elevenplay','','','2018-04-19 12:58:05','2018-04-19 19:58:05','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=115',0,'tribe_events','',0),(116,3,'2017-12-12 19:55:27','2017-12-12 19:55:27','','ElevenPlay_660x340','','inherit','closed','closed','','elevenplay_660x340','','','2018-04-04 11:40:23','2018-04-04 18:40:23','',115,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/ElevenPlay_660x340.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(117,3,'2017-12-12 19:57:54','2017-12-12 19:57:54','The story has been told before but never like this: An occupied desert nation; a radical from the wilderness on hunger strike; a girl whose mysterious dance will change the course of the world.\r\n\r\nThis charged retelling turns the infamous biblical tale on its head, placing the girl we call Salom at the center of a revolution. Internationally acclaimed theatre director Yal Farber (Les Blancs) draws on multiple accounts to create her urgent, hypnotic production on the stage of the National Theatre.\r\n\r\nNOTE: This is not a live performance; it is a high-definition film of the stage production captured live at Britains National Theatre.\r\n\r\nTicket sale is coming soon.','National Theatre Live Series  Salom','Director Yal Farber moves away from earlier misogynistic interpretations of the biblical myth and casts Salom as a symbol of persecuted womanhood who acquires political agency (The Guardian).','publish','closed','closed','','national-theatre-live-series-salome','','','2018-04-19 12:56:02','2018-04-19 19:56:02','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=117',0,'tribe_events','',0),(118,3,'2017-12-12 19:58:24','2017-12-12 19:58:24','','NTLive_Salome_Listings_Landscape_International-Lisa-Laymon-e1502740486192','','inherit','closed','closed','','ntlive_salome_listings_landscape_international-lisa-laymon-e1502740486192','','','2018-04-04 11:40:20','2018-04-04 18:40:20','',117,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/NTLive_Salome_Listings_Landscape_International-Lisa-Laymon-e1502740486192.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(119,3,'2017-12-12 20:02:29','2017-12-12 20:02:29','Emery Entertainment and the Hammer Theatre present <i>Menopause The Musical</i>, the longest-running off-Broadway production in Las Vegas and an international hit show. Playing for 16 consecutive years, it continues to make audiences laugh at Harrah\'s Hotel and Casino on the Strip. The musical has toured across the world in more than 450 U.S. cities and nearly 300 international cities in 15 countries.\r\n\r\nRave reviews from the <i>New York Times</i> and <i>LA Times</i> praise <i>Menopause</i> for being witty and hilarious: Its impossible not to laugh at the fresh, funny, and simply terrific musical. Viewers have described the musical as a <i>Rocky Horror Picture Show</i> that celebrates women. And members of all genders love the performance with one male patron pronouncing Menopause as a mandatory humor workshop for men.\r\n\r\nOn stage, the cast makes fun of their woeful hot flashes, mood swings, and night sweats as they bring down the house with musical parodies of classic tunes from the 60s, 70s, and 80s.\r\n\r\nKaren Gedissman, who plays the Iowa housewife, says that the show is a tribute to women and real sisterhood. She has known audiences who leave the show feeling like they have truly bonded with the actors on stage.\r\n\r\nThis musical has so much humor and so much heart, Gedissman says. Its not just funnyits enlightening and transformational.\r\n\r\nCome celebrate the bond between women and the changes that they go through in their lives.\r\n\r\nThe Hammer has partnered with Emery Entertainment to bring more off-Broadway productions, including Robert Dubacs <i>The Book of Moron</i> (March 29-31) and <i>Late Nite Catechism</i> (May 18-20). They will also be bringing Michael Ingersolls Artists Lounge Live featuring <i>Elvis: My Way</i> (Feb. 23-24).','Menopause The Musical','GFour Productions celebrates women going through The Change in this hilarious musical comedy. The 90-minute musical gets audience members out of their seats and singing along to parodies of classic pop songs. ','publish','closed','closed','','menopause-the-musical','','','2018-04-19 12:44:30','2018-04-19 19:44:30','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=119',0,'tribe_events','',0),(120,3,'2017-12-12 20:02:10','2017-12-12 20:02:10','','Menopause_calendar','','inherit','closed','closed','','menopause_calendar','','','2018-04-04 11:40:06','2018-04-04 18:40:06','',119,'