 journey with one simple question: Who am I? What do I believe? Whats the point? Okay, thats three questions but suffice to say, he has no answers. Just voices. Inner voices that come to life with precision and wit. And one by one, the voices pull him into a hysterical alternative universe of critical thought in search of the bigger picture.\r\n\r\nIf you are yearning for some satire that cuts with a shrewd, sharp edge or are just plumb tired of adolescent comedies generated by the mediocrity of television, then buckle up for a hilarious joy ride with The Book of Moron.','Robert Dubac\'s The Book of Moron','Robert Dubacs newest off-Broadway hit, The Book of Moron, has been described as one of the most hilarious, intelligent, and scorching satirical attacks on idiocracy since Mark Twain.','publish','closed','closed','','robert-dubacs-the-book-of-moron','','','2018-03-19 19:12:44','2018-03-20 02:12:44','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=155',0,'tribe_events','',0),(156,3,'2018-01-10 19:23:33','2018-01-10 19:23:33','','book_moron','','inherit','closed','closed','','book_moron','','','2018-04-04 11:39:27','2018-04-04 18:39:27','',155,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/book_moron.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(157,3,'2018-01-10 20:31:33','2018-01-10 20:31:33','Part catechism class, part stand-up routine,<em>Late Nite Catechism</em>is an uproariously funny comedy in which the audience are students in Sister\'s class. Shell take you back to the days of the Latin Mass, meatless Fridays, and remind you about that good old ruler across the knuckles!\r\n\r\nThis interactive comedy appeals to Catholics and non-Catholics alike since Sister clearly explains religious references in lighthearted ways while maintaining a serious tone that isnt too preachy and far from being saccharine. (<i>The Catholic Register</i>)\r\n\r\nAnd <i>The New York Times</i> raves about the show, calling it an inspired, will-written, and hilarious piece.\r\n\r\nCome to the Hammer to watch <i>Late Nite Catechism</i> for a night of fun.','Late Nite Catechism','Part catechism class, part stand-up routine, <em>Late Nite Catechism</em> is an uproariously funny comedy in which the audience are students in Sister\'s class.','publish','closed','closed','','late-nite-catechism','','','2018-05-01 12:22:04','2018-05-01 19:22:04','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=157',0,'tribe_events','',0),(158,3,'2018-01-10 20:31:27','2018-01-10 20:31:27','','EE_LNC_thumb','','inherit','closed','closed','','ee_lnc_thumb','','','2018-04-04 11:39:25','2018-04-04 18:39:25','',157,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/EE_LNC_thumb.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(160,3,'2018-01-11 22:09:52','2018-01-11 22:09:52','','top','','inherit','closed','closed','','top','','','2018-04-04 11:39:17','2018-04-04 18:39:17','',109,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/top.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(161,3,'2018-01-11 22:24:35','2018-01-11 22:24:35','','Screen Shot 2018-01-11 at 2.24.05 PM','','inherit','closed','closed','','screen-shot-2018-01-11-at-2-24-05-pm','','','2018-04-04 11:39:15','2018-04-04 18:39:15','',109,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Screen-Shot-2018-01-11-at-2.24.05-PM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(162,3,'2018-01-11 22:34:13','2018-01-11 22:34:13','','Screen Shot 2018-01-11 at 2.31.09 PM','','inherit','closed','closed','','screen-shot-2018-01-11-at-2-31-09-pm','','','2018-04-04 11:39:13','2018-04-04 18:39:13','',109,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Screen-Shot-2018-01-11-at-2.31.09-PM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(163,3,'2018-01-11 22:34:14','2018-01-11 22:34:14','','Screen Shot 2018-01-11 at 2.31.02 PM','','inherit','closed','closed','','screen-shot-2018-01-11-at-2-31-02-pm','','','2018-04-04 11:39:12','2018-