tre.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=462',0,'tribe_events','',0),(463,4,'2018-03-12 17:52:29','2018-03-12 17:52:29','Director Simon Stone reinvents Federico Garca Lorcas classic, <em>Yerma</em>, for the modern English stage--which The Times describes as an extraordinary theatrical triumph.\r\n\r\nStarring the incredible Billie Piper (<em>Penny Dreadful, Doctor Who</em>), Yerma delves into the story of a young woman driven to madness in her attempt to conceive. Her desperation for a child builds with elemental force to a staggering, shocking, climax.\r\nPipers performance is raw, ferocious, spellbinding (<em>Evening Standard</em>). And her portrayal of Yerma is one of all-consuming despair, with sharply witty, slangily modern updating (<em>The Daily Mail</em>).','Yerma  Billie Piper (National Theatre Live)','Starring the incredible Billie Piper <em>(Penny Dreadful, Doctor Who)</em>, this modern interpretation of Yerma delves into the story of a young woman driven to madness in her attempt to conceive.','publish','closed','closed','','yerma-billie-piper-national-theatre-live','','','2018-04-19 12:55:41','2018-04-19 19:55:41','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=463',0,'tribe_events','',0),(465,4,'2018-03-12 18:00:45','2018-03-12 18:00:45','August 1947. The Partition of India and Pakistan.\r\n15 million people displaced. 2 million dead.\r\n\r\nA provocative and compelling performance woven from innumerable true life accounts blending theatre, dance, music and multimedia. A retrospective lens into the greatest mass displacement in human history.\r\n\r\nOn the 70th anniversary of the Partition, EnActe Arts and Noorani Dance brings you, through dance, music and storytelling, the true life stories of the people who lived through the Partition of Greater India into India, Pakistan and subsequently Bangladesh.The Parting is inspired by true stories from witnesses of the 1947 Partition of India and Pakistan. This performance is a chance to reflect on this pivotal and tragic time in the history of South Asia, and provoke dialogue across generations, borders, genders, ethnicities and religions.\r\n\r\nWritten by Salil Singh &amp; Anurag Wadehra\r\nDirected by Vinita Sud Belani &amp; Farah Yasmeen Shaikh\r\nMusic Composer Raaginder Singh Momi\r\nVisual Director David Murakami\r\nProject Manager Pratiksha Shah\r\nProduction Manager YuMee Jang\r\nOriginally Directed by Salil Singh','The Parting','A provocative and compelling performance woven from innumerable true life accounts blending theatre, dance, music and multimedia.','publish','closed','closed','','the-parting','','','2018-03-15 14:34:34','2018-03-15 21:34:34','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=465',0,'tribe_events','',0),(467,4,'2018-03-12 18:10:00','2018-03-12 18:10:00','World-renowned Speed Painter Vilas Nayak and acclaimed Indian classical dancer Aarthy Sundar showcase an explosion of colors on canvas, an art miracle, heart pounding music, imagination and thought--provoking storytelling through dance.\r\n\r\nProceeds benefit non-profit Empower And Excels efforts to bring smiles and color to the lives of underprivileged children.','Art with a Heart','World-renowned Speed Painter Vilas Nayak and acclaimed Indian classical dancer Aarthy Sundar showcase an art miracle, heart pounding music, imagination, and thought-provoking storytelling. ','publish','closed','closed','','art-with-a-heart','','','2018-04-19 12:48:56','2018-04-19 19:48:56','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=467',0,'tribe_events','',0),(470,4,'2018-03-14 16:43:48','2018-03-14 16:43:48','','694x390_1_estatic_waters','','inherit','closed','closed','','694x390_1_estatic_waters','','','2018-04-04 11:32:07','2018-04-04 18:32:07','',236,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/694x390_1_estatic_waters.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(471,4,'2018-0