 The Imitation Game) takes on the title role of Shakespeares great tragedy. As a country arms itself for war, a royal family tears itself apart.','publish','closed','closed','','hamlet-benedict-cumberbatch-national-theatre-live','','','2018-04-19 12:56:49','2018-04-19 19:56:49','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=494',0,'tribe_events','',0),(495,4,'2018-03-14 18:00:19','2018-03-14 18:00:19','Caesar returns in triumph to Rome and the people pour out of their homes to celebrate. Alarmed by the autocrats popularity, the educated lite conspire to bring him down. After his assassination, civil war erupts on the streets of the capital.\r\n\r\nNicholas Hytners production thrusts the audience into the street party that greets Caesars return, the congress that witnesses his murder, the rally that assembles for his funeral and the chaos that explodes in its wake.\r\n\r\nBen Whishaw (<em>The Danish Girl, Skyfall, Hamlet</em>) and Michelle Fairley (<em>Fortitude, Game of Thrones</em>) play Brutus and Cassius. David Calder (<em>The Lost City of Z, The Hatton Garden Job</em>) plays Caesar and David Morrissey (<em>The Missing, Hangmen, The Walking Dead</em>) is Mark Antony.\r\n\r\n<strong>NOTE: This is not a live performance; it is a high-definition screening of the stage production captured live at London\'s Bridge Theatre.</strong>','Julius Caesar  Ben Whishaw, Michelle Fairley','Broadcast from London, Nicholas Hytners production will thrust the audience into the street party that greets Caesars return, the congress that witnesses his murder, the rally that assembles for his funeral, and the chaos that explodes in its wake.','publish','closed','closed','','julius-caesar-ben-whishaw-michelle-fairley-national-theatre-live','','','2018-04-19 12:54:24','2018-04-19 19:54:24','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=495',0,'tribe_events','',0),(496,4,'2018-03-14 18:04:03','2018-03-14 18:04:03','Europes most feared terrorist is hiding in Dean Street, Soho. Broke, restless, and horny, the 32 year-old revolutionary is a frothing combination of intellectual brilliance, invective, satirical wit, and child-like emotional literacy.\r\n\r\nCreditors, spies, rival revolutionary factions, and prospective seducers of his beautiful wife all circle like vultures. His writing blocked, his marriage dying, his friend Engels in despair at his wasted genius, his only hope is a job on the railway.\r\n\r\nBut theres still no one in the capital who can show you a better night on the piss than Karl Heinrich Marx.\r\n\r\nRory Kinnear (The Threepenny Opera, Penny Dreadful, Othello) is Marx and Oliver Chris (Twelfth Night, Green Win) is Engels, in this comedy written by Richard Bean and Clive Coleman.\r\n\r\n<strong>NOTE: This is not a live performance; it is a high-definition screening of the stage production captured live at London\'s Bridge Theatre.</strong>','Young Marx  Rory Kinnear, Oliver Chris','Europes most feared terrorist is hiding in Dean Street, Soho. Broke, restless, and horny, the 32 year-old revolutionary is a frothing combination of intellectual brilliance, invective, satirical wit, and child-like emotional literacy.','publish','closed','closed','','young-marx-rory-kinnear-oliver-chris-national-theatre-live','','','2018-04-19 12:55:18','2018-04-19 19:55:18','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=496',0,'tribe_events','',0),(502,7,'2018-03-14 13:52:14','2018-03-14 20:52:14','The SJSU Wind Ensemble presents an entire concert inspired by water in poetry on Tuesday, March 20 at the Hammer Theatre. The program includes Ara Batur by Sigur Ros and Ecstatic Waters by Steven Bryant. It will also feature the premiere of Anthropogenic Tides by Tina Tallon for live electronics and wind ensemble, a composition that uses climate change data in its creation to illustrate the grave dangers of rising sea levels. This is a concert not to be missed!','Ecstatic Waters <br> SJSU Wind ensemble','The SJSU Wind Ensemble presents an entire concert inspired by water in poetry on Tuesday, March 20 at the Hammer Theatre.','inherit','closed','closed','','462-autosave-v1','','','2018-03-14 13:52:14','2018-03-14 20:52:14','',462,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/2018/03/462-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(504,7,'2018-03-14 14:07:52','2018-03-14 21:07:52','','noche','','inherit','closed','closed','','noche','','','2018-04-04 11:31:12','2018-04-04 18:31:12','',410,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/noche.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(505,7,'2018-03-14 14:17:17','2018-03-14 21:17:17','','3x6 Hammer Graphic - Lisa Laymon','','inherit','closed','closed','','3x6-hammer-graphic-lisa-laymon','','','2018-04-04 11:31:06','2018-04-04 18:31:06','',465,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/3x6-Hammer-Graphic-Lisa-Laymon.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(506,7,'2018-03-14 14:22:12','2018-03-14 21:22:12','','Art with a Heart','','inherit','closed','closed','','art-with-a-heart-2','','','2018-04-04 11:31:02','2018-04-04 18:31:02','',467,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Art-with-a-Heart.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(509,7,'2018-03-15 14:01:45','2018-03-15 21:01:45','San Jos State University students collaborate with San Jos native and vocal consultant Jesse Sanchez from the national tour of <i>Hamilton</i> to bring you the Broadway hit, <i>In the Heights</i>, by Lin-Manuel Miranda. Hammer Theatre patrons can enjoy the original Broadway set converted for this university production.\r\n\r\n<i>In the Heights</i> tells the story of a Hispanic-American neighborhood of Washington Heights in New York City.\r\n\r\nTold as a series of interweaving vignettes about the highs and lowsand the dreams and realitiesof life in the neighborhood, <i>In the Heights</i> offers audiences a very likable three-day glimpse into a specific multi-generational Latinx experience that not only feels fresh and new but also feels remarkably relatable no matter what background you come from (<i>Onstage Blog</i>).\r\n\r\nThe characters are relatable and charming, full of triumph and angst as they struggle to reach the elusive American Dream. The play blends a variety of catchy tunes with a score featuring hip-hop, salsa, merengue, and soul music.\r\n\r\nThe <i>New York Times</i> praises Lin-Manuel Miranda as a gifted young composer for creating a singing mural of Latin-American life that often has the inspiriting flavor of a morning pick-me-up on a warm summer day. Light and sweet are actually just the words to describe this amiable show, which boasts an infectious, bouncy Latin-pop score.\r\n\r\nAnd the <i>Theatre Guide Review</i> calls this Broadway a winning musical lottery ticket to local theatergoers...an abundance of talent, technical expertise, a solid score, and humanity in the story that makes <i>In the Heights</i> a must-see experience.\r\n\r\nCome see this famous musical that speaks with hope and song to the dream of succeeding in America!\r\n\r\nThis university production is directed by Buddy butler, produced by Barnaby Dallas, and conducted by Fred Cohen.','In The Heights SJSU Film & Theatre, SJSU School of Music & Dance','San Jos State University students collaborate with San Jos native and vocal consultant Jesse Sanchez from the national tour of <i>Hamilton</i> to bring you the Broadway hit, <i>In the Heights</i>, by Lin-Manuel Miranda.','publish','closed','closed','','in-the-heights-sjsu-film-theatre-sjsu-school-of-music-dance','','','2018-05-04 11:39:24','2018-05-04 18:39:24','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=509',0,'tribe_events','',0),(510,7,'2018-03-15 13:55:53','2018-03-15 20:55:53','','InTheHeights_goldstar','','inherit','closed','closed','','intheheights_goldstar','','','2018-04-04 11:31:00','2018-04-04 18:31:00','',509,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/InTheHeights_goldstar.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(517,7,'2018-03-15 14:15:47','2018-03-15 21:15:47','','InTheHeights_goldstar (1)','','inherit','closed','closed','','intheheights_goldstar-1','','','2018-04-04 11:30:57','2018-04-04 18:30:57','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/InTheHeights_goldstar-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(519,7,'2018-03-15 14:27:25','2018-03-15 21:27:25','','Grupo Folklorico logo for Facebook','','inherit','closed','closed','','grupo-folklorico-logo-for-facebook','','','2018-04-04 11:30:53','2018-04-04 18:30:53','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Grupo-Folklorico-logo-for-Facebook.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(520,7,'2018-03-15 14:27:47','2018-03-15 21:27:47','Noche Folklrico Luna y Sol de San Jos State is a student organization exemplifying the ongoing commitment to diversity of San Jos State University. Students work towards the promotion, education, and preservation of Mexican culture through Mexican folkloric dance. Student have been recognized by San Jos Mayor Chuck Reed and the City of San Jos for their work in building culture and community at San Jos State and the surrounding area. Dancers represent a wide range of academic disciplines and have dedicated themselves to being cultural ambassadors in high education and beyond. Viva San Jos State! Viva Mxico!','Noche Folklrico <br> Luna y Sol de SJSU <br> 15th Anniversary Celebration','Noche Folklrico Luna y Sol de San Jos State is a student organization exemplifying the ongoing commitment to diversity of San Jos State University.','inherit','closed','closed','','410-autosave-v1','','','2018-03-15 14:27:47','2018-03-15 21:27:47','',410,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/2018/03/410-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(521,7,'2018-03-15 14:30:24','2018-03-15 21:30:24','','EnE-FB-banner-Hammer-V1 - Lisa Laymon','','inherit','closed','clos