anales Project (TCP) brings a musical celebration of extraordinary women to the Hammer Theatre. This concert commemorates honorees such as Hillary Clinton, Chief Theresa Kachindamoto, Sister Marilyn Lacey, Michelle Obama, Justice Sonia Sotomayo, and more. \r\n\r\nLed by Kurt Crowley, also the music director of Broadways Hamilton, talented composers and musical artists collaborate to create original songs delivering new and powerful insights into the nature of womens leadership and the challenges women face.\r\n\r\n','Carla Canales Hear Her Song','Created to celebrate stories of remarkable women, <i>Hear Her Song</i> brings together an extraordinary array of musical artists, offering powerful insights into womens leadership worldwide.\r\n','publish','closed','closed','','carla-canales-hear-her-song','','','2018-04-27 13:08:14','2018-04-27 20:08:14','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=556',0,'tribe_events','',0),(558,7,'2018-03-22 20:10:15','2018-03-23 03:10:15','<h3>SJSU Center for Literary Arts</h3>\r\n<h4><em>Lewandowski Poet</em></h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe Center for Literary Arts celebrates National Poetry Month with Peter Balakian and President Mary Papazian at the Hammer Theatre.\r\n\r\nPeter Balakian recently won the 2016 Pulitzer Prize for <i>Ozone Journal </i>which recounts the speakers experience in excavating bones of victims of Armenian genocide in the Syrian desert. His writing has received praise from critics and readers alike. For <i>Ozone Journal</i>, the Pulitzer Prize committee praises Balakian for bearing witness to the old losses and tragedies that undergird a global age of danger and uncertainty.\r\n\r\nAs a writer, Balakian pulls from his experience as an Armenian American. He became inspired to explore and reconnect with his Armenian heritage after learning that his grandmother was a survivor of the Syrian Death March. Since this discovery, Balakian has been writing to unearth his familys legacy and to study the relationship between the Armenian Genocides and the Armenian Diaspora.\r\n\r\nPresiden Mary Papazian will join the stage after Peter Balakian. She became SJSUs 30th president in 2016. Since her inaugural, she has been committed to student success and building a campus of cultural and intellectual diversity. Papazian is responsible for the appointment of a chief diversity officer to lead a newly-established Office of Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion at SJSU. As an Armenian American, Mary Papazian will provide insight and engage in a dialogue about the importance of diversity with Peter Balakian.\r\n\r\nClick <a style=\"color: blue; text-decoration: underline !important;\" href=\"http://www.litart.org/peter-balakian/\">here</a> to read more','Peter Balakian  Pulitzer Series','Celebrate National Poetry Month with Peter Balakian who recently won the 2016 Pulitzer Prize for Ozone Journal recounting the speakers experience in excavating bones of victims of Armenian genocide in the Syrian desert. ','publish','closed','closed','','peter-balakian-pulitzer-prize-writers-series','','','2018-04-19 12:53:19','2018-04-19 19:53:19','',0,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=558',0,'tribe_events','',0),(561,3,'2018-03-23 12:39:48','2018-03-23 19:39:48','','Peter Balakian_graphics','','inherit','closed','closed','','peter-balakian_graphics','','','2018-04-02 11:42:25','2018-04-02 18:42:25','',558,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Peter-Balakian_graphics.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(562,3,'2018-03-23 12:39:51','2018-03-23 19:39:51','','Peter Balakian_banner','','inherit','closed','closed','','peter-balakian_banner','','','2018-04-02 11:42:35','2018-04-02 18:42:35','',558,'http://hammertheatre.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Peter-Balakian_banner.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(565,3,'2018-03-24 01:12:16','2018-03-24 08:12:16','','More','','publish','closed','closed','','more',